ni was unable to ban sales by immigrant mobile food vendors. The Guide takes us to the place where the Dutch tried to ban street side sales by Scottish peddlers 350 years ago, and where the great Fiorello La Guardia banned most of the pushcart salesmen at midcentury. But Kamil and Wakin are not nostalgists or preservationists. Instead, their historical tours connect today's city with the snapshots of yesterday, blending social and cultural history with the evolution of different ethnic and cultural communities. The Big Onion Guide includes ten walking tours, plus a 5-borough driving tour, peppered with informative sidebars, illustrations, and photos from the collection at the New-York Historical Society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aTravel / United States / Northeast / Middle Atlantic (NJ, NY, PA).2bisacsh  aApple.  aCity.  aLong.  aOnion.  aYork.  abefore.  acalled.  adubbed.  aknew.  athose.1 aJackson, Kenneth T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Kenneth.1 aKamil, Seth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWakin, Eric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWakin, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479800131423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479800131.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  